to encourage people to create their own stop-motion shorts.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":5,"endDate":{"day":22,"month":4,"year":2015},"episodes":3,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Drama","Fantasy"],"id":107110,"idMal":22661,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":59,"season":"WINTER","seasonYear":2014,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/107110","startDate":{"day":19,"month":1,"year":2014},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Banpresto's \"Cry Heart\" Short","Fuyujima ni Furu Sakura","Children's Dream","Ace no Saigo "],"title":{"native":"ワンピース Cry heart","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Cry heart","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Cry heart"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"OTHER"},{"node":{"countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1c9ae","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b107256-Pvgk6VnCmMZq.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b107256-Pvgk6VnCmMZq.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b107256-Pvgk6VnCmMZq.png"},"description":"A special that was part of many animated multi-screen Panic Adventure crossovers of Shueisha manga series that have been screened at special events called \"Odaiba Boken-Oh\" (お台場冒険王; lit. \"Odaiba Adventure King\") in Japan. These events were held from 2003 to 2008 to commemorate Fuji TV's 45th anniversary.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\nThe crossover was featured exclusively at the Fuji TV headquarters in the Kyutai (orb) section, where smaller screens partially surrounded the audience watching, each showing a point of view, while a bigger one would be used for close-ups.\u003cbr\u003e","duration":9,"endDate":{"year":2004},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action"],"id":107256,"idMal":23935,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":47,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/107256","startDate":{"year":2004},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Orb Panic Adventure Returns!","Сфера панического приключения: Возвращение"],"title":{"native":"球体パニックアドベンチャーリターンズ!!!","romaji":"Kyutai Panic Adventure Returns!!!","userPreferred":"Kyutai Panic Adventure Returns!!!"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n2385-kYxcxwV0LTvq.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#fef10d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx2385-06iBj9aNIadt.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx2385-06iBj9aNIadt.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx2385-06iBj9aNIadt.jpg"},"description":"Luffy and his crew are on Mirror Ball Island during a dance carnival. They are spotted by Marines just as Jango the hypnotist is running from them. Luffy and the others are caught up in the dance carnival as Jango, in his desperate attempt to escape, hypnotizes the entire island to dance the night away.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":6,"endDate":{"day":3,"month":3,"year":2001},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":2385,"idMal":2385,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":67,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2001,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/2385","startDate":{"day":3,"month":3,"year":2001},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"One Piece: Django's Dance Carnival","native":"ONE PIECE ねじまき島の冒険 ジャンゴのダンスカーニバル","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Nejimaki-jima no Bouken - Jango no Dance Carnival","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Nejimaki-jima no Bouken - Jango no Dance Carnival"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/101099-KarIxewMysiK.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#a1a135","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b101099-3AoCbJWTj2cV.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b101099-3AoCbJWTj2cV.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b101099-3AoCbJWTj2cV.jpg"},"description":"Series of commercials launched by Nissin Foods' Cup Noodles brand. Among some original content, the commercials also featured characters from prominent anime series including:\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n- Kiki's Delivery Service\u003cbr\u003e\n- Heidi: Girl of the Alps\u003cbr\u003e\n- Sazae-san\u003cbr\u003e\n- One Piece\n","duration":1,"endDate":{"day":7,"month":2,"year":2020},"episodes":11,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Romance","Slice of Life"],"id":101099,"idMal":35770,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":62,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/101099","startDate":{"day":7,"month":6,"year":2017},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Hungry Days: Yokoku-hen","Hungry Days: Majo no Takkyuubin-hen","Hungry Days: Heidi-hen","Hungry Days: Sazae-san-hen","Hungry Days: One Piece","Hungry Days: Zoro-hen","Hungry Days: Nami-hen","Hungry Days: Vivi-hen","Hungry Days: Choujou Gibasen-hen"],"title":{"native":"HUNGRY DAYS　アオハルかよ。","romaji":"HUNGRY DAYS: Aoharu ka yo.","userPreferred":"HUNGRY DAYS: Aoharu ka yo."},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/21880-9gGzVvnzqiNA.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4a135","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx21880-uxsZ880LXSdY.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx21880-uxsZ880LXSdY.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx21880-uxsZ880LXSdY.jpg"},"description":"A short prequel to One Piece Film: Gold featuring the nine Straw hat crew members on the ship, planning what to do when they arrive the Casino.","duration":10,"endDate":{"day":2,"month":7,"year":2016},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":21880,"idMal":33606,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2016,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/21880","startDate":{"day":2,"month":7,"year":2016},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"native":"ONE PIECE FILM GOLD 〜episode 0〜 711ver.","romaji":"ONE PIECE FILM: GOLD - episode 0 711ver.","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE FILM: GOLD - episode 0 711ver."},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/5252-tlTORLa2dR2u.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#43a1e4","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/5252.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/5252.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/5252.jpg"},"description":"The Straw Hat Pirates, searching for the great passage \"Grand Line\", are in trouble when their food runs out! Luffy, searching for food on his own, finds a ship belonging to the pirate, Gary, and takes it over!! He lands at a nearby town...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nLuffy was attacked by a young girl, Silk, who mistook him for a member of the other pirate gang. As the two eat a meal, they tell their stories. Meanwhile, Gary and his band are burning with anger at Luffy, demanding payment from the town's defenseless citizens...!!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Jumpland)","duration":33,"endDate":{"day":24,"month":11,"year":2008},"episodes":1,"format":"OVA","genres":["Action","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":5252,"idMal":5252,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2008,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/5252","startDate":{"day":24,"month":11,"year":2008},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Prototype"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Romance Dawn Story","native":"ONE PIECE ロマンス ドーン ストーリー","romaji":"ONE PIECE: ROMANCE DAWN STORY","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: ROMANCE DAWN STORY"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"ALTERNATIVE"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/n30793-SDlOKsKEVHxa.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1ae5d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx30793-Zca4SIWG5j8e.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx30793-Zca4SIWG5j8e.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/small/bx30793-Zca4SIWG5j8e.png"},"description":"A collection of short stories drawn by Oda Eiichiro before One Piece became a major hit. \nIncludes:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nWanted! (1992) \u003cbr\u003e\nGod's Gift for the Future (1993) \u003cbr\u003e\nIkki Yakou (1993) \u003cbr\u003e\nMonsters (1994) \u003cbr\u003e\nRomance Dawn (Version 2, 1996) \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nTo celebrate the 20th anniversary of the One Piece TV anime, Romance Dawn version 2 was adapted into a TV special. (Episode 907)","endDate":{},"format":"MANGA","genres":["Action","Comedy"],"id":30793,"idMal":793,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/manga/30793","startDate":{"day":4,"month":11,"year":1998},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["원티드(WANTED!)"],"title":{"english":"Wanted! Eiichiro Oda Before One Piece ","native":"WANTED！ 尾田栄一郎短編集","romaji":"WANTED! Oda Eiichiro Tanpenshuu","userPreferred":"WANTED! Oda Eiichiro Tanpenshuu"},"trailer":{"id":"3uaMeEcwvvU","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3uaMeEcwvvU/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"MANGA"},"relationType":"SOURCE"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/113308-jvwBxZ1dJcVx.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1865d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx113308-u6wWW3d01DSt.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx113308-u6wWW3d01DSt.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx113308-u6wWW3d01DSt.jpg"},"description":"A collaboration between Nissin Cup Noodles HUNGRY DAYS campaign x rock group BUMP OF CHICKEN: a full-fledged music video directed by Kyotarou Hayashi for the song \u003ci\u003eKinen Satsuei\u003c/i\u003e by BUMP OF CHICKEN. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThe music video follows the series of One Piece-themed \"Hungry Days: Aoharu ka yo.\" commercials in a what-if world of Luffy's Straw Hat Pirates if they were living as high school students. The theme of the video is about graduation, where the Straw Hat Pirates recollect the days of encounters, farewells, and adolescence through photos taken in their pasts. ","duration":5,"endDate":{"day":2,"month":11,"year":2019},"episodes":1,"format":"MUSIC","genres":["Drama"],"id":113308,"idMal":52139,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":77,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/113308","startDate":{"day":2,"month":11,"year":2019},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["HUNGRY DAYS × BUMP OF CHICKEN 「記念撮影」MV","HUNGRY DAYS × BUMP OF CHICKEN - Kinen Satsuei","HUNGRY DAYS × BUMP OF CHICKEN - Commemorative Photo","One Piece x BUMP OF CHICKEN","Hungry Days: One Piece"],"title":{"native":"記念撮影","romaji":"Kinen Satsuei","userPreferred":"Kinen Satsuei"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/114761-cgU5ZD6nQ911.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#0dbbfe","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b114761-C2xOMuA44zKY.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b114761-C2xOMuA44zKY.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b114761-C2xOMuA44zKY.png"},"description":"Eiichiro Oda's One Piece manga is collaborating with the japanese boy band Arashi on a music video to be released on January 4. Jun Matsumoto from Arashi commented that the timing of the collaboration was chosen to coincide with both the One Piece anime and Arashi's 20th anniversaries.","duration":4,"endDate":{"day":4,"month":1,"year":2020},"episodes":1,"format":"MUSIC","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy"],"id":114761,"idMal":40970,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":58,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/114761","startDate":{"day":4,"month":1,"year":2020},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"native":"A-RA-SHI : Reborn","romaji":"A-RA-SHI : Reborn","userPreferred":"A-RA-SHI : Reborn"},"trailer":{"id":"woqtlIbFJGU","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/woqtlIbFJGU/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n10033-u9ROjiLizrd4.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#50aef1","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx10033-V7xnlgAVtaVR.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx10033-V7xnlgAVtaVR.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx10033-V7xnlgAVtaVR.jpg"},"description":"In the world where the taste and texture of food are very important there is Toriko, a hunter of precious foods regularly hired by restaurants and the rich. A man with inhuman skills to capture the ferocious, evasive and rare animals to complete his ultimate dinner course and then the chef Komatsu, his current accomplice: a weak timid person who was inspired by Toriko's greatness and accompanies him on all his journeys on his quest for the course of his life.","duration":24,"endDate":{"day":30,"month":3,"year":2014},"episodes":147,"format":"TV","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":10033,"idMal":10033,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":69,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2011,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/10033","startDate":{"day":3,"month":4,"year":2011},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Toriko (2011)","Toriko (TV)","Toriko x One Piece Collabo Special"],"title":{"native":"トリコ","romaji":"Toriko","userPreferred":"Toriko"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/813-03ZLvWJgR6Wd.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e49343","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx813-ZhnFNOeCU5dQ.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx813-ZhnFNOeCU5dQ.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx813-ZhnFNOeCU5dQ.png"},"description":"Goku is back with his new son, Gohan, but just when things are getting settled down, the adventures continue. Whether he is facing enemies such as Freeza, Cell, or Boo, Goku is proven to be an elite of his own and discovers his race, Saiyan. He meets many new people, gaining allies as well as enemies, as he still finds time to raise a family and be the happy-go-lucky Saiyan he is.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":24,"endDate":{"day":31,"month":1,"year":1996},"episodes":291,"format":"TV","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy","Supernatural"],"id":813,"idMal":813,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":80,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":1989,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/813","startDate":{"day":26,"month":4,"year":1989},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["DBZ","Dragonball Z","דרגון בול זי","What's My Destiny Dragon Ball","ดราก้อนบอล Z","Bảy Viên Ngọc Rồng Z","Драконий жемчуг Зет"],"title":{"english":"Dragon Ball Z","native":"ドラゴンボールZ","romaji":"Dragon Ball Z","userPreferred":"Dragon Ball Z"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/126649-pxeImm81vD6l.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e48628","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b126649-sbuKTAghtsln.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b126649-sbuKTAghtsln.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b126649-sbuKTAghtsln.jpg"},"description":"A Tokyo One Piece Tower exclusive film. It's a tie-in to a real treasure hunting event in collaboration with Takarush Corp. for a limited time called Treasure Hunting: Tongari Shima no Daibouken. During this, you’ll decipher the mysteries of ancient documents found by Luffy, Usopp, and Chopper, and then set out to find the nest of the mysterious animal known as Tongari Ton!\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThe film itself begins at the end of your treasure hunting adventure at the Tokyo One Piece Tower, where the Straw Hat Crew are tricked into opening a chest in a cave thinking it's where the Tongari Island treasure is.\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Otakumode)","duration":10,"endDate":{"day":1,"month":11,"year":2016},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy"],"id":126649,"idMal":38419,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":63,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2016,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/126649","startDate":{"day":1,"month":11,"year":2016},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Treasure Hunting: Tongari Shima no Daibouke"],"title":{"english":"The Great Tongari Island Treasure Hunting Adventure","native":"東京ワンピースタワー トンガリ島の大秘宝","romaji":"Tokyo One Piece Tower: Tongari Shima no Dai Hihou","userPreferred":"Tokyo One Piece Tower: Tongari Shima no Dai Hihou"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/134184-My4zIFu5a4j1.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#fe9350","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx134184-25CEkbRJEzXB.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx134184-25CEkbRJEzXB.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/small/bx134184-25CEkbRJEzXB.png"},"description":"This is the second version of \"Romance Dawn\" containing 45 pages, and was originally published in the Weekly Shonen Jump of 1996 issue #41 on 23 September. It has since been reprinted, along with a page of author commentary, in the Eiichiro Oda early-works compilation Wanted! in 1998.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ci\u003eNote: It was adapted into episode 907 of the One Piece TV anime that aired on October 20, 2019.\u003c/i\u003e","endDate":{"day":23,"month":9,"year":1996},"format":"ONE_SHOT","genres":["Action","Comedy","Drama"],"id":134184,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":72,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/manga/134184","startDate":{"day":23,"month":9,"year":1996},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Romance Dawn - Version 2"],"title":{"english":"Romance Dawn","native":"ロマンスドーン","romaji":"Romance Dawn","userPreferred":"Romance Dawn"},"type":"MANGA"},"relationType":"SOURCE"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/141902-SvnRSXnN7DWC.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1c950","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx141902-fTyoTk8F8qOl.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx141902-fTyoTk8F8qOl.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx141902-fTyoTk8F8qOl.jpg"},"description":"\u003ci\u003eAn almighty voice. With fiery red locks.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThe story takes place on an island where Uta, the world’s favorite diva, performs for the first time in public. Uta’s singing voice, which she sings with while concealing her true identity, has been described as “otherworldly,” and while the venue is filled with the Straw Hats led by Luffy, pirates, navy, and fans from all over the world who have come to enjoy her voice, Uta’s voice is heard in a new light. The curtain rises on the story with the shocking revelation that she is “Shanks’ daughter!“ \n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: ONE PIECE FILM RED Website)\n","duration":115,"endDate":{"day":6,"month":8,"year":2022},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy","Music"],"id":141902,"idM